name: I DON'T WANT IT!
description:
Episode 3 of the series "feel my pain"

"Yesterday you threw stones at me and now you touch my body".
Weak people always be the object of violence.
The object of sexual abuse, sexual assault, sexual harassment, and rape. They can't act because they are weak.
Not only physically but also on their social media too.
It still happens and it still hurts just as much.
They didn't dare to speak up.
Because if they speak up, the “world” will just say "it's just a normal thing, you're just too sensitive".
And their pain is getting worse and worse.
Is all this thing we can call it normal?
